             Ghana and 10-man Australia are tied
1-1 in the second half of their World Cup Group D match in
Rustenburg, South Africa.  
 Australiaâ€™s Harry Kewell received a red card in the 24th
minute for a handball on the goal line. Asamoah Gyan scored with
the penalty kick to tie the game after Brett Holman put
Australia ahead in the 11th minute.  
 The Netherlands beat Japan 1-0 earlier and Cameroon faces
Denmark later today in Group E games.  
          
          


  


        